<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747220>
    dc:description "Figure 33. Tyloporella reussi Voigt. (a,b) Upper Cenomanian (Actinocamax plenus zone), Hoher Stein Quarry in Dresden-Plauen, Saxony, Germany; (a) holotype, MMG SaK 1617; part of colony with two broken ovicells indicated by arrows. (b) MMG SaK 15777a; autozooids and avicularia at growing edge. (c) NMP, Novak Collection (figured Novak 1877, pl. 1, fig. 19, 20 as Membranipora irregularis (von Hagenow)); Late Cretaceous,?Turonian, Kamajka, Bohemia, Czech Republic; autozooids and avicularia; an autozooid with the opesia covered by a closure plate is arrowed. (d) NHMUK BZ 8221; Cretaceous. Late Cenomanian or early Turonian, Kaňk, Central Bohemian Region, Czech Republic; autozooids (some with closure plates) and avicularia. Scale bars = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4747220/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

